==English==
The Van de Graaff generator was invented in 1931 by the American physicist Robert Jemison Van de Graaff.
This device was initially used to generate electrsostatic charge for particle accelerators.
The vdg is a constant current source whuch means it supplies a constant to all appliances connected to it (as against a battery which is a constant voltage source)
===Etymology===
from [[w:Robert J. Van de Graaff|Robert Jemison Van de Graaff]] who developed it
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''[[Van der Graaff]] [[generator]]'''
#{{physics}} a [[device]] in which an [[electric]] [[charge]] is built up on a large [[spherical]] [[electrode]] by means of a rapidly moving [[belt]]